    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Mizner</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 26, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Blaine instructs Mr. Mizner immediately to tender the good offices of this
                    Government for the friendly adjustment of all the differences among the states
                    of Central America, and adds that our action is prompted by impartial and
                    earnest friendship, and that, while we desire not to exercise any constraint, it
                    is our wish to make an end of a situation not only destructive of the peace of
                    our neighbors, but of injury to the common interests of all.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
